Both required outputs are in place.

- `transcript.json` — schema-validated, 10 iterations, 80 hypotheses, 81 analyses (each with `hypothesis_ids`, `effect_estimate`, `p_value`, `significant`, and code/result-summary fields).
- `analysis_summary.txt` — narrative walkthrough of all 10 iterations, what was supported vs. refuted, and overall conclusions.

Headline findings: a multivariable OLS on 28 covariates explains R²=0.97 of pfs_months. Dominant signed effects are age (+0.17/yr — counter-intuitively positive), ECOG (-1.15/grade), albumin (+0.48/g·dL⁻¹), log(PSA) (-0.38), weight-loss% (-0.077), log(LDH) (-0.10). The single clinically actionable treatment-biomarker interaction is **olaparib × BRCA2 mutation** (+1.55 mo univariate within BRCA2+, p=4e-27; +1.64 mo adjusted, p=4e-76). Lu177-PSMA × PSMA-high, pembrolizumab × MSI-high, and AR-V7 × enzalutamide/abiraterone interactions were all not significant. No race/ethnicity, insurance, or comorbidity main effects detected. Among 25 SNPs, none survived Bonferroni correction.
